MRtrix 3.0.5                      ddwwii22rreessppoonnssee

     ddwwii22rreessppoonnssee: part of the MRtrix3 package

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS

     Estimate response function(s) for spherical deconvolution

UUSSAAGGEE

     _d_w_i_2_r_e_s_p_o_n_s_e algorithm [ options ] ...

        _a_l_g_o_r_i_t_h_m    Select the algorithm to be used to complete the script operation;
                     additional details and options become available once an
                     algorithm is nominated. Options are: dhollander, fa,
                     manual, msmt_5tt, tax, tournier

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

     dwi2response offers different algorithms for performing various types of
     response function estimation. The name of the algorithm must appear as the
     first argument on the command-line after 'dwi2response'. The subsequent
     arguments and options depend on the particular algorithm being invoked.

     Each algorithm available has its own help page, including necessary
     references; e.g. to see the help page of the 'fa' algorithm, type
     'dwi2response fa'.

OOppttiioonnss  ffoorr  iimmppoorrttiinngg  tthhee  ddiiffffuussiioonn  ggrraaddiieenntt  ttaabbllee

  _-_g_r_a_d GRAD
     Provide the diffusion gradient table in MRtrix format

  _-_f_s_l_g_r_a_d bvecs bvals
     Provide the diffusion gradient table in FSL bvecs/bvals format

GGeenneerraall  ddwwii22rreessppoonnssee  ooppttiioonnss

  _-_m_a_s_k MASK
     Provide an initial mask for response voxel selection

  _-_v_o_x_e_l_s VOXELS
     Output an image showing the final voxel selection(s)

  _-_s_h_e_l_l_s SHELLS
     The b-value(s) to use in response function estimation (comma-separated list
     in case of multiple b-values, b=0 must be included explicitly)

  _-_l_m_a_x LMAX
     The maximum harmonic degree(s) for response function estimation (comma-
     separated list in case of multiple b-values)

AAddddiittiioonnaall  ssttaannddaarrdd  ooppttiioonnss  ffoorr  PPyytthhoonn  ssccrriippttss

  _-_n_o_c_l_e_a_n_u_p
     do not delete intermediate files during script execution, and do not delete
     scratch directory at script completion.

  _-_s_c_r_a_t_c_h /path/to/scratch/
     manually specify the path in which to generate the scratch directory.

  _-_c_o_n_t_i_n_u_e <ScratchDir> <LastFile>
     continue the script from a previous execution; must provide the scratch
     directory path, and the name of the last successfully-generated file.

SSttaannddaarrdd  ooppttiioonnss

  _-_i_n_f_o
     display information messages.

  _-_q_u_i_e_t
     do not display information messages or progress status. Alternatively, this
     can be achieved by setting the MRTRIX_QUIET environment variable to a non-
     empty string.

  _-_d_e_b_u_g
     display debugging messages.

  _-_f_o_r_c_e
     force overwrite of output files.

  _-_n_t_h_r_e_a_d_s number
     use this number of threads in multi-threaded applications (set to 0 to
     disable multi-threading).

  _-_c_o_n_f_i_g key value  (multiple uses permitted)
     temporarily set the value of an MRtrix config file entry.

  _-_h_e_l_p
     display this information page and exit.

  _-_v_e_r_s_i_o_n
     display version information and exit.

